China (Yunnan, Hainan), Vietnam (
Fleutiaux 1931
).

Female.
Color like male. Apex of abdominal ventrite V tri-lobed; with shape of middle lobe semicircular to longitudinal with apex rounded; deeply to gently incised between middle and lateral lobes (Fig. 
9D-G
). [In non-type specimens: proximal sclerites of bursa copulatrix ovoid (Fig. 
8I
), with shallow basal concavity; apex acute, each with 8-11 large spines on convex mesal edge, 15-17 smaller spines on disc.]
